{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nTicket 3b4e's close FAILed twice with the unmet criteria surfaced piecemeal — round 1 named one coverage gap, round 2 a different one — costing two extra Gerrit/CI cycles (changes 526, 527). A FAIL verdict should be complete: every unmet criterion enumerated with its remediation in one pass, so one remediation round can clear the gate.\n\n## What\n- Update the completion-verifier rubric prompt (src/rebar/llm/reviewers/completion_verifier.md) to require exhaustive evaluation: assess EVERY acceptance/success/close criterion independently and, on FAIL, emit one finding per unmet criterion — never stop at the first failure. State explicitly that a verdict naming only a subset of unmet criteria is an incomplete verdict.\n- This is a pass-4/prompt-level change: no verdict-reconciliation or threshold logic changes (rebar.llm.completion.reconcile_verdict stays byte-identical).\n- Prove the behavior with an EVAL case, not a tautological FakeRunner test. A FakeRunner unit test only returns pre-loaded findings, so it cannot demonstrate the prompt achieves exhaustive evaluation (reconcile_verdict already passes multi-findings through by construction). Add to `src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/completion-verifier.eval.yaml`: (a) a new deterministic scorer `enumerates_all_unmet_criteria` — on a case whose fixture ticket has N independently-unmet criteria, assert the FAIL verdict emits a distinct finding for EACH (>= N findings, each naming a different criterion); (b) a dataset case `CV-two-unmet-criteria` (expect: fail) with a fixture ticket carrying exactly two independent AC gaps (e.g. an unimplemented function AND an untested path). This is the live-eval behavioral proof (runs under the [eval] extra in eval CI).\n- Additionally add a FakeRunner unit test (mirror tests/interfaces/store/test_completion_verifier.py) asserting the PLUMBING invariant: a multi-finding FAIL verdict survives reconcile_verdict and the close path with all findings intact (guards against regression in the pass-through, distinct from the prompt-behavior eval above).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The completion-verifier prompt (completion_verifier.md, Verdict & findings section) requires per-criterion exhaustive evaluation and one finding per unmet criterion on FAIL, and states that a verdict naming only a subset of unmet criteria is an incomplete verdict.\n- [ ] completion-verifier.eval.yaml gains the `enumerates_all_unmet_criteria` scorer AND the `CV-two-unmet-criteria` case (two independently-unmet criteria) whose scorer asserts BOTH appear as separate findings in one verdict. Offline `validate_eval_spec(strict=True)` passes on the extended spec.\n- [ ] A FakeRunner unit test asserts a two-finding FAIL verdict is preserved (all findings intact) through reconcile_verdict + the close path.\n- [ ] reconcile_verdict and the close-path logic are byte-unchanged (no reconciliation/threshold edits).\n- [ ] make lint passes on the change.\n- [ ] make test passes on the change."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783888544725891001,"uuid":"da001d44-5978-45ba-996a-291fdd8b71d3"}